All young men from the 80s should have this.

The picture is grainy and lettering is blurry, just as I would expect from upscaled DVD. Having stated this, both of these are among my favorite movies, and well worth the price. I just wish they were of noticeably better quality than with a DVD upscaled by my blu-ray player.

I have always wanted a copy of both these films, because when I first saw them I found them great. Now, they are together on one Blu-ray disc. See listing for details about the individual movies, all I will say is they stand the test of time, and are among the best of their type. Get yours today!
Where's the original Spring Break on blu ray with Perry Lang and a soundtrack that includes 38 Special and Cheap Trick? These two movies suck compared to that one.
